      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of being trapped by looming responsibilities is incredibly suffocating, and it makes perfect sense that you feel hopeless. When the walls feel that high, the idea of finding a way through them can seem impossible. Instead of trying to fix the whole life, perhaps you could focus only on the smallest, most immediate thing you can change today—even if it's just a single small step. There is a way to ease the pressure, even if it's just a tiny shift in perspective.",
      "source": "target",
